==English==
===Etymology 1===
possibly from [[triumph]]

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌmp|-ʌmp]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
#(''in plural'') the [[suit]], in a [[game]] of [[cards]], that [[outrank]]s all others
#:''Diamonds were declared '''trumps'''.''
# a [[playing card]] of that suit
#:''He played an even higher '''trump'''.''
#(''by extension'') something that gives one an [[advantage]], especially one held in [[reserve]]
# (''vulgar slang'') the noise and/or smell resulting from the expulsion of methane from the [[anus]].

====Verb====
'''to trump'''
# to [[play]] a trump, or to take a [[trick]] with a trump; to [[ruff]]
# to [[get the better of]], or [[finesse]], a [[competitor]]
# ''(vulgar slang)'' to audibly expel air from the [[anus]]
#:''"Blimey, I've just '''trumped'''.''"

